{"parentUuid":"88a6fd60-7e15-4fc9-a819-3c7983e5274d","isSidechain":true,"promptId":"b6d534eb-f80d-405a-a05d-4c7eb6280654","agentId":"a6b206ed2a9ee5b50","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01GiRBvfhfMCPq7vvKxx74QD","type":"tool_result","content":"307:## Test strategy\n309:**`pyramid`** (the project default). The unit tier carries the boundary logic that needs no database:\n531:- **Tests pass at >= 85% coverage** → ✓ *Test strategy* + `acceptance.md` (every AC maps to a named","is_error":false}]},"uuid":"bf0ba785-41b3-4044-9e1e-d0c926425044","timestamp":"2026-07-10T03:24:38.695Z","sourceToolAssistantUUID":"88a6fd60-7e15-4fc9-a819-3c7983e5274d","userType":"external","entrypoint":"claude-vscode","cwd":"c:\\Users\\brett\\OneDrive\\Documents\\GitHub\\meterly-pipeline-test","sessionId":"cb1e5971-0f87-4706-9a1d-09f830df9e6f","version":"2.1.205","gitBranch":"feature/quota-admin"}
{"parentUuid":"405860a9-c432-44e2-bf0d-f012371811e8","isSidechain":true,"promptId":"b6d534eb-f80d-405a-a05d-4c7eb6280654","agentId":"a6b206ed2a9ee5b50","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01KoGQckGt7Tso9cxUBpXcaM","type":"tool_result","content":"# Plan — quota administration (list + delete)\n\nAuthoritative brief: `.pipeline/requirements.md` (operator-elicited; Resolved / Open / Out-of-scope).\nEvery Resolved item below is turned into scope + an acceptance criterion; the brief has **zero Open\nitems** (the operator confirmed the defaults explicitly), and the Out-of-scope items are hard\nexclusions that are **not** planned. Design source: none (backend HTTP API — no UI to build).\n\n## Summary\n\nMeterly already lets an admin-scoped key create-or-replace a per-customer, per-metric usage cap via\n`PUT /v1/quotas` (feature \"metric-quotas\", shipped). This feature completes the quota-admin CRUD by\nadding the two read/remove surfaces on the **same path**, gated by the **same** admin dependency\nchain and scoped to the **same** tenant model:\n\n1. **`GET /v1/quotas`** (new, admin-scoped) — returns the full, unpaginated list of the caller's own\n   tenant's quotas, deterministically ordered by `(customer_id, metric)`, each row the minimal\n   `{customer_id, metric, limit_per_window}` field set (identical to the existing `QuotaResponse`).\n2. **`DELETE /v1/quotas?customer_id=X&metric=Y`** (new, admin-scoped) — removes the cap for one\n   `(customer_id, metric)` in the caller's tenant. **204 No Content** on success; **404** (standard\n   error envelope) when no such quota exists in the caller's tenant (explicit, not silently\n   idempotent). Query parameters only, no request body.\n\nThe core approach is **extend, don't reinvent**: reuse the `_require_admin_and_throttled` dependency\n(auth → Tier-2 throttle → admin-scope gate), reuse the exact anchored `CustomerId`/`Metric`\nallowlists PUT already validates against, reuse `scoped_transaction` (which sets the RLS session\nsetting), and reuse the `quotas` table and its `quotas_tenant_isolation` FORCE-RLS policy that\nmigration `0003` already installed. No new table, **no new Alembic migration**, no new cloud\ninfrastructure, no new credential, and — critically — **no change to `POST /v1/events`**: deleting a\nquota removes only the cap, never touching recorded `usage_rollup` usage. The scanner/auth context\nstays the existing `Authorization: Bearer mtr_live_<key_id>_<secret>` split-token.\n\nWhy this is a genuine micro-change and not a rewrite: every layer already exists and already isolates\nby `api_key_id`. GET adds one ordered `SELECT`; DELETE adds one parameterized `DELETE … RETURNING`;\nboth hang off the existing route module and its existing admin dependency. The only net-new\ncorrectness surfaces are (a) the DELETE-not-found → 404 decision, (b) the query-param validation\ncontract for DELETE, and (c) safe-error / fail-closed handling on the two new DB-I/O paths (the\ngeneric `500` envelope + transaction rollback) — all three covered explicitly below and in the threat\nmodel.\n\n## Stack notes\n\nAssessed each default against this project; every choice **endorses the existing Meterly stack**\nrecorded in `CLAUDE.md`. This is a brownfield increment onto a shipped feature, so consistency with\nthe established stack is the overriding consideration and each default already fits — there is no\ndivergence for the checkpoint to ratify, only the confirmation below.\n\n- **Language / framework:** Python 3.12 + FastAPI + async SQLAlchemy `text()` repositories — endorsed\n  (matches every existing module and the sibling `PUT /v1/quotas` code this extends).\n- **Database:** PostgreSQL (RDS) — endorsed; the feature reads and deletes rows in the existing\n  `quotas` table using boring, proven primitives (`SELECT … ORDER BY`, `DELETE … RETURNING`). DDIA\n  note: no new storage/messaging surface, so no replication/partitioning/consistency question arises\n  — this is single-node transactional CRUD on an existing indexed table.\n- **Migrations:** Alembic — endorsed, **but not exercised**: no schema change, so **no new revision**.\n  The `quotas` table, its PK `(api_key_id, customer_id, metric)`, its `CHECK`, and its FORCE-RLS\n  policy all already exist from revision `0003`. Adding a migration here would be dead DDL.\n- **Auth:** existing API-key facade + the `scope` column (`ingest`/`admin`) — endorsed and reused\n  unchanged. Both new routes reuse the existing `_require_admin_and_throttled` dependency verbatim; no\n  new scope, provider, token type, or MFA path.\n- **Cloud / IaC:** AWS + Terraform — **no change**. The feature provisions nothing (`iac-conventions`\n  not triggered — no `infra/` resource). It reads/deletes rows in the existing RDS instance.\n- **Observability / logging:** structlog facade + CloudWatch/X-Ray + Sentry — endorsed; the feature\n  emits **one** new structured event (`quota.delete`) and reuses the existing `quota.forbidden`.\n- **Runtime secrets:** unchanged — no new credential consumed (`secrets-management` not triggered).\n\n## Backend\n\n### `GET /v1/quotas` — the tenant's full quota list\n\n- *What:* a new handler on the existing `src/api/routes/quotas.py` router,\n  `@router.get(\"/v1/quotas\", response_model=list[QuotaResponse])`, depending on the existing\n  `_require_admin_and_throttled`. It calls a new service `list_tenant_quotas(principal)` that opens a\n  `scoped_transaction(principal.api_key_id)` and calls a new repository `list_quotas(session,\n  api_key_id)`, returning `list[QuotaResponse]`.\n- *Why full/unpaginated (not paginated or filtered):* the brief resolves this explicitly — per-tenant\n  quota counts are expected to stay small (bounded by the admin's own `PUT` calls, one row per\n  `(customer, metric)`), so pagination/filtering would be speculative machinery for a set that fits in\n  one response. Pagination is a hard out-of-scope exclusion. Rejected alternative — a\n  `limit`/`offset` or cursor scheme — adds an input surface, an ordering-stability contract across\n  pages, and tests, for zero benefit at the expected cardinality.\n- *Why `response_model=list[QuotaResponse]` (the minimal field set):* the response echoes only\n---\n  506 tests/integration/test_quotas_list_delete.py\n  151 tests/test_schemas_quotas.py\n  229 tests/integration/test_quotas_rls_backstop.py\n  886 total","is_error":false}]},"uuid":"ebf806c8-f349-424e-9921-3ef823a6b62c","timestamp":"2026-07-10T03:24:46.030Z","sourceToolAssistantUUID":"405860a9-c432-44e2-bf0d-f012371811e8","userType":"external","entrypoint":"claude-vscode","cwd":"c:\\Users\\brett\\OneDrive\\Documents\\GitHub\\meterly-pipeline-test","sessionId":"cb1e5971-0f87-4706-9a1d-09f830df9e6f","version":"2.1.205","gitBranch":"feature/quota-admin"}
{"parentUuid":"ebf806c8-f349-424e-9921-3ef823a6b62c","isSidechain":true,"agentId":"a6b206ed2a9ee5b50","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-5","id":"msg_011CcsfMphHtfLzU7F9csCoF","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01UxLjUqMUDWRL6LTv4uoKem","name":"Read","input":{"file_path":"c:\\Users\\brett\\OneDrive\\Documents\\GitHub\\meterly-pipeline-test\\.pipeline\\plan.md","offset":300,"limit":40},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":122,"cache_creation_input_tokens":2721,"cache_read_input_tokens":32385,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":2721,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":34,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null},"requestId":"req_011CcsfMoapUyoDDjqbC5Ur1","attributionAgent":"testing","type":"assistant","uuid":"db35e5c7-33be-46c7-adf0-1baad1e19ca6","timestamp":"2026-07-10T03:24:48.857Z","userType":"external","entrypoint":"claude-vscode","cwd":"c:\\Users\\brett\\OneDrive\\Documents\\GitHub\\meterly-pipeline-test","sessionId":"cb1e5971-0f87-4706-9a1d-09f830df9e6f","version":"2.1.205","gitBranch":"feature/quota-admin"}
{"parentUuid":"db35e5c7-33be-46c7-adf0-1baad1e19ca6","isSidechain":true,"promptId":"b6d534eb-f80d-405a-a05d-4c7eb6280654","agentId":"a6b206ed2a9ee5b50","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01UxLjUqMUDWRL6LTv4uoKem","type":"tool_result","content":"300\t- `CLAUDE.md` — note `GET`/`DELETE /v1/quotas` alongside the existing `PUT` in the auth line.\n301\t\n302\t**Task decomposition:** the implementation change set is **7 files** (6 modified + 1 created source/\n303\ttest files above; docs are a separate stage). That is below the ≥8-file threshold, so **no\n304\t`tasks.md`** is emitted — this builds single-shot from `plan.md`, extending existing modules with a\n305\trepo function pair, a service function pair, two route handlers, and one query-param schema.\n306\t\n307\t## Test strategy\n308\t\n309\t**`pyramid`** (the project default). The unit tier carries the boundary logic that needs no database:\n310\t`QuotaDeleteParams` validation (allowlist, injection/oversized rejection, `extra='forbid'`) in\n311\t`tests/test_schemas_quotas.py`, and the 404-vs-204 decision is a thin mapping best proven end-to-end.\n312\tA **focused integration tier** against the real Postgres + Redis testcontainers (existing `conftest`)\n313\tcovers the guarantees that are only real against actual Postgres — deterministic ordering over a\n314\tseeded multi-row set, the empty-list case, tenant isolation for both GET and DELETE (the FORCE-RLS\n315\tbackstop + `api_key_id` filter), the DELETE 204/404 contract, the safe-error / fail-closed 500 path\n316\t(forced internal error → generic envelope, no partial delete), the two-principals-one-IP throttle\n317\tdimension, and the \"delete removes the cap but never resets `usage_rollup`, and `POST /v1/events`\n318\tun-caps cleanly\" cross-behavior. E2E stays minimal (the route round-trips are the integration tier).\n319\tThis is a bias toward exercising the real datastore for the tenancy/ordering guarantees, still under\n320\tthe unchanged `>= 85%` branch-coverage gate — not a relaxation of it.\n321\t\n322\t## Open questions\n323\t\n324\t1. **GET list read-logging.** The plan emits **no** dedicated business-audit log for `GET /v1/quotas`\n325\t   (a read of the caller's own config; mirrors `GET /v1/usage`, which logs no business event). DELETE\n326\t   *is* logged (`quota.delete`). *Proposed default:* keep GET unlogged. Confirm at the checkpoint, or\n327\t   add a light `quota.list` INFO (count only, no `customer_id`) if admin-read auditing is desired.\n328\t2. **Ordering collation.** `ORDER BY customer_id, metric` yields a **deterministic** order every call\n329\t   (the requirement), using the RDS default text collation. *Proposed default:* do not add\n330\t   `COLLATE \"C\"` — the requirement is *deterministic* order (guaranteed by `ORDER BY`), not\n331\t   byte-identical order across differing collations, and there is a single RDS collation in this\n332\t   deployment. Confirm, or add `COLLATE \"C\"` if cross-environment byte-stable ordering is later\n333\t   required.\n334\t\n335\t## Threat Model\n336\t\n337\tMethod: STRIDE (Shostack), scoped to **this feature** (GET list + DELETE). Each credible threat names\n338\ta **concrete mechanism** (library/config/SQL construct + the file it lives in) and the **ASVS 5.0.0**\n339\trequirement it satisfies. Most controls are **reused, already-verified** mechanisms from the shipped"}]},"uuid":"f54981c9-53f4-4101-95ba-ff37ca38f185","timestamp":"2026-07-10T03:24:48.898Z","sourceToolAssistantUUID":"db35e5c7-33be-46c7-adf0-1baad1e19ca6","userType":"external","entrypoint":"claude-vscode","cwd":"c:\\Users\\brett\\OneDrive\\Documents\\GitHub\\meterly-pipeline-test","sessionId":"cb1e5971-0f87-4706-9a1d-09f830df9e6f","version":"2.1.205","gitBranch":"feature/quota-admin"}
{"parentUuid":"f54981c9-53f4-4101-95ba-ff37ca38f185","isSidechain":true,"agentId":"a6b206ed2a9ee5b50","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-5","id":"msg_011CcsfMphHtfLzU7F9csCoF","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_013Y9xuk4EWioxbpNw6LyzYr","name":"Read","input":{"file_path":"c:\\Users\\brett\\OneDrive\\Documents\\GitHub\\meterly-pipeline-test\\tests\\integration\\test_quotas_list_delete.py"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":122,"cache_creation_input_tokens":2721,"cache_read_input_tokens":32385,"output_tokens":233,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":2721},"inference_geo":"not_available","iterations":[{"input_tokens":122,"output_tokens":233,"cache_read_input_tokens":32385,"cache_creation_input_tokens":2721,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":2721,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"type":"message"}],"speed":"standard"},"diagnostics":null},"requestId":"req_011CcsfMoapUyoDDjqbC5Ur1","attributionAgent":"testing","type":"assistant","uuid":"f1d9050f-2adc-4b3a-9354-11efb92030a8","timestamp":"2026-07-10T03:24:49.084Z","userType":"external","entrypoint":"claude-vscode","cwd":"c:\\Users\\brett\\OneDrive\\Documents\\GitHub\\meterly-pipeline-test","sessionId":"cb1e5971-0f87-4706-9a1d-09f830df9e6f","version":"2.1.205","gitBranch":"feature/quota-admin"}
{"parentUuid":"f1d9050f-2adc-4b3a-9354-11efb92030a8","isSidechain":true,"promptId":"b6d534eb-f80d-405a-a05d-4c7eb6280654","agentId":"a6b206ed2a9ee5b50","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_013Y9xuk4EWioxbpNw6LyzYr","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t\"\"\"Integration tests for `GET /v1/quotas` (list) and `DELETE /v1/quotas`\n2\tagainst a real Postgres + Redis (AC1-AC17, AC19; AC18 is delegated to the\n3\tsecurity stage's ASVS reconciliation).\n4\t\"\"\"\n5\t\n6\timport asyncio\n7\t\n8\tfrom httpx import ASGITransport, AsyncClient\n9\tfrom sqlalchemy import text\n10\t\n11\t\n12\tdef _put_payload(**overrides) -> dict:\n13\t    payload = {\"customer_id\": \"cust_1\", \"metric\": \"api_calls\", \"limit_per_window\": 1000}\n14\t    payload.update(overrides)\n15\t    return payload\n16\t\n17\t\n18\tasync def _seed_quota(client, headers, **overrides) -> None:\n19\t    \"\"\"Create a quota via the existing PUT endpoint — reusing the already-proven\n20\t    write path rather than inserting rows directly keeps these tests focused on\n21\t    the new GET/DELETE behavior.\"\"\"\n22\t    response = await client.put(\"/v1/quotas\", json=_put_payload(**overrides), headers=headers)\n23\t    assert response.status_code in (200, 201)\n24\t\n25\t\n26\tasync def test_get_lists_tenant_quotas_ordered_minimal_fields(client, make_api_key):\n27\t    \"\"\"AC1: GET returns the full unpaginated list, ordered by (customer_id,\n28\t    metric), each row exactly {customer_id, metric, limit_per_window}.\"\"\"\n29\t    presented_key, _ = await make_api_key(scope=\"admin\")\n30\t    headers = {\"Authorization\": f\"Bearer {presented_key}\"}\n31\t\n32\t    # Seed out of order so the response ordering is actually proven, not\n33\t    # merely echoing insertion order.\n34\t    await _seed_quota(client, headers, customer_id=\"cust_b\", metric=\"api_calls\", limit_per_window=200)\n35\t    await _seed_quota(client, headers, customer_id=\"cust_a\", metric=\"storage_gb\", limit_per_window=50)\n36\t    await _seed_quota(client, headers, customer_id=\"cust_a\", metric=\"api_calls\", limit_per_window=100)\n37\t\n38\t    response = await client.get(\"/v1/quotas\", headers=headers)\n39\t\n40\t    assert response.status_code == 200\n41\t    body = response.json()\n42\t    assert body == [\n43\t        {\"customer_id\": \"cust_a\", \"metric\": \"api_calls\", \"limit_per_window\": 100},\n44\t        {\"customer_id\": \"cust_a\", \"metric\": \"storage_gb\", \"limit_per_window\": 50},\n45\t        {\"customer_id\": \"cust_b\", \"metric\": \"api_calls\", \"limit_per_window\": 200},\n46\t    ]\n47\t    for row in body:\n48\t        assert set(row.keys()) == {\"customer_id\", \"metric\", \"limit_per_window\"}\n49\t\n50\t\n51\tasync def test_get_is_tenant_isolated(client, make_api_key):\n52\t    \"\"\"AC2: tenant A's list contains only tenant A's rows, never tenant B's.\"\"\"\n53\t    key_a, _ = await make_api_key(label=\"tenant-a\", scope=\"admin\")\n54\t    key_b, _ = await make_api_key(label=\"tenant-b\", scope=\"admin\")\n55\t    headers_a = {\"Authorization\": f\"Bearer {key_a}\"}\n56\t    headers_b = {\"Authorization\": f\"Bearer {key_b}\"}\n57\t\n58\t    await _seed_quota(client, headers_a, customer_id=\"cust_a\", limit_per_window=100)\n59\t    await _seed_quota(client, headers_b, customer_id=\"cust_b\", limit_per_window=200)\n60\t\n61\t    response_a = await client.get(\"/v1/quotas\", headers=headers_a)\n62\t    assert response_a.status_code == 200\n63\t    body_a = response_a.json()\n64\t    assert len(body_a) == 1\n65\t    assert body_a[0][\"customer_id\"] == \"cust_a\"\n66\t\n67\t\n68\tasync def test_get_empty_returns_200_empty_list(client, make_api_key):\n69\t    \"\"\"AC3: no quotas -> 200 with an empty array, never 404.\"\"\"\n70\t    presented_key, _ = await make_api_key(scope=\"admin\")\n71\t\n72\t    response = await client.get(\n73\t        \"/v1/quotas\", headers={\"Authorization\": f\"Bearer {presented_key}\"}\n74\t    )\n75\t\n76\t    assert response.status_code == 200\n77\t    assert response.json() == []\n78\t\n79\t\n80\tasync def test_get_ingest_key_forbidden(client, make_api_key):\n81\t    \"\"\"AC4: an ingest-scoped key gets 403 `forbidden` on GET — admin scope required.\"\"\"\n82\t    presented_key, _ = await make_api_key(scope=\"ingest\")\n83\t\n84\t    response = await client.get(\n85\t        \"/v1/quotas\", headers={\"Authorization\": f\"Bearer {presented_key}\"}\n86\t    )\n87\t\n88\t    assert response.status_code == 403\n89\t    assert response.json()[\"error\"][\"code\"] == \"forbidden\"\n90\t\n91\t\n92\tasync def test_get_requires_auth(client):\n93\t    \"\"\"AC5: missing/malformed auth -> 401 on GET.\"\"\"\n94\t    response = await client.get(\"/v1/quotas\")\n95\t    assert response.status_code == 401\n96\t\n97\t    response = await client.get(\n98\t        \"/v1/quotas\", headers={\"Authorization\": \"Bearer not-a-real-token\"}\n99\t    )\n100\t    assert response.status_code == 401\n101\t\n102\t\n103\tasync def test_delete_existing_returns_204_and_removes_row(client, make_api_key, postgres_url):\n104\t    \"\"\"AC6: DELETE of an existing quota -> 204 empty body; the row is gone\n105\t    from a subsequent GET and from the table directly.\"\"\"\n106\t    presented_key, api_key_id = await make_api_key(scope=\"admin\")\n107\t    headers = {\"Authorization\": f\"Bearer {presented_key}\"}\n108\t    await _seed_quota(client, headers, customer_id=\"cust_1\", metric=\"api_calls\")\n109\t\n110\t    response = await client.delete(\n111\t        \"/v1/quotas\", params={\"customer_id\": \"cust_1\", \"metric\": \"api_calls\"}, headers=headers\n112\t    )\n113\t\n114\t    assert response.status_code == 204\n115\t    assert response.content == b\"\"\n116\t\n117\t    listing = await client.get(\"/v1/quotas\", headers=headers)\n118\t    assert listing.json() == []\n119\t\n120\t    from sqlalchemy.ext.asyncio import create_async_engine\n121\t\n122\t    engine = create_async_engine(postgres_url)\n123\t    async with engine.connect() as connection:\n124\t        count = (\n125\t            await connection.execute(\n126\t                text(\"SELECT COUNT(*) FROM quotas WHERE api_key_id = :id\"), {\"id\": api_key_id}\n127\t            )\n128\t        ).scalar_one()\n129\t    await engine.dispose()\n130\t    assert count == 0\n131\t\n132\t\n133\tasync def test_delete_absent_returns_404_envelope(client, make_api_key):\n134\t    \"\"\"AC7: DELETE of a (customer_id, metric) with no quota -> 404 not_found,\n135\t    the standard error envelope (explicit, not silently idempotent).\"\"\"\n136\t    presented_key, _ = await make_api_key(scope=\"admin\")\n137\t\n138\t    response = await client.delete(\n139\t        \"/v1/quotas\",\n140\t        params={\"customer_id\": \"cust_missing\", \"metric\": \"api_calls\"},\n141\t        headers={\"Authorization\": f\"Bearer {presented_key}\"},\n142\t    )\n143\t\n144\t    assert response.status_code == 404\n145\t    assert response.json()[\"error\"][\"code\"] == \"not_found\"\n146\t\n147\t\n148\tasync def test_delete_cannot_touch_other_tenant(client, make_api_key, postgres_url):\n149\t    \"\"\"AC8: tenant A deleting a (customer_id, metric) that exists only under\n150\t    tenant B -> 404 (invisible), and tenant B's row is still present.\"\"\"\n151\t    key_a, _ = await make_api_key(label=\"tenant-a\", scope=\"admin\")\n152\t    key_b, api_key_id_b = await make_api_key(label=\"tenant-b\", scope=\"admin\")\n153\t    headers_a = {\"Authorization\": f\"Bearer {key_a}\"}\n154\t    headers_b = {\"Authorization\": f\"Bearer {key_b}\"}\n155\t\n156\t    await _seed_quota(client, headers_b, customer_id=\"cust_shared\", metric=\"api_calls\", limit_per_window=500)\n157\t\n158\t    response = await client.delete(\n159\t        \"/v1/quotas\", params={\"customer_id\": \"cust_shared\", \"metric\": \"api_calls\"}, headers=headers_a\n160\t    )\n161\t    assert response.status_code == 404\n162\t\n163\t    from sqlalchemy.ext.asyncio import create_async_engine\n164\t\n165\t    engine = create_async_engine(postgres_url)\n166\t    async with engine.connect() as connection:\n167\t        row = (\n168\t            await connection.execute(\n169\t                text(\"SELECT limit_per_window FROM quotas WHERE api_key_id = :id\"),\n170\t                {\"id\": api_key_id_b},\n171\t            )\n172\t        ).mappings().one()\n173\t    await engine.dispose()\n174\t    assert row[\"limit_per_window\"] == 500\n175\t\n176\t\n177\tasync def test_delete_validation_rejections(client, make_api_key):\n178\t    \"\"\"AC9: missing/invalid/injection/unknown-extra query params -> 422 validation_failed.\"\"\"\n179\t    presented_key, _ = await make_api_key(scope=\"admin\")\n180\t    headers = {\"Authorization\": f\"Bearer {presented_key}\"}\n181\t\n182\t    missing_metric = await client.delete(\n183\t        \"/v1/quotas\", params={\"customer_id\": \"cust_1\"}, headers=headers\n184\t    )\n185\t    assert missing_metric.status_code == 422\n186\t    assert missing_metric.json()[\"error\"][\"code\"] == \"validation_failed\"\n187\t\n188\t    bad_customer_id = await client.delete(\n189\t        \"/v1/quotas\", params={\"customer_id\": \"bad id with spaces\", \"metric\": \"api_calls\"}, headers=headers\n190\t    )\n191\t    assert bad_customer_id.status_code == 422\n192\t\n193\t    injection = await client.delete(\n194\t        \"/v1/quotas\", params={\"customer_id\": \"' OR 1=1--\", \"metric\": \"api_calls\"}, headers=headers\n195\t    )\n196\t    assert injection.status_code == 422\n197\t\n198\t    extra_param = await client.delete(\n199\t        \"/v1/quotas\",\n200\t        params={\"customer_id\": \"cust_1\", \"metric\": \"api_calls\", \"api_key_id\": \"999\"},\n201\t        headers=headers,\n202\t    )\n203\t    assert extra_param.status_code == 422\n204\t\n205\t\n206\tasync def test_delete_ingest_key_forbidden(client, make_api_key):\n207\t    \"\"\"AC10: an ingest-scoped key gets 403 `forbidden` on DELETE.\"\"\"\n208\t    presented_key, _ = await make_api_key(scope=\"ingest\")\n209\t\n210\t    response = await client.delete(\n211\t        \"/v1/quotas\",\n212\t        params={\"customer_id\": \"cust_1\", \"metric\": \"api_calls\"},\n213\t        headers={\"Authorization\": f\"Bearer {presented_key}\"},\n214\t    )\n215\t\n216\t    assert response.status_code == 403\n217\t    assert response.json()[\"error\"][\"code\"] == \"forbidden\"\n218\t\n219\t\n220\tasync def test_delete_requires_auth(client):\n221\t    \"\"\"AC11: missing/malformed auth -> 401 on DELETE.\"\"\"\n222\t    response = await client.delete(\n223\t        \"/v1/quotas\", params={\"customer_id\": \"cust_1\", \"metric\": \"api_calls\"}\n224\t    )\n225\t    assert response.status_code == 401\n226\t\n227\t    response = await client.delete(\n228\t        \"/v1/quotas\",\n229\t        params={\"customer_id\": \"cust_1\", \"metric\": \"api_calls\"},\n230\t        headers={\"Authorization\": \"Bearer not-a-real-token\"},\n231\t    )\n232\t    assert response.status_code == 401\n233\t\n234\t\n235\tasync def test_quota_admin_routes_rate_limited_per_principal(truncate_tables, make_api_key):\n236\t    \"\"\"AC12: both GET and DELETE /v1/quotas are Tier-2 per-api_key_id rate\n237\t    limited; two admin principals sharing one client IP get independent\n238\t    buckets (mirrors test_quotas_endpoint.py::test_put_rate_limited_per_principal).\"\"\"\n239\t    from src.main import app\n240\t\n241\t    key_a, _ = await make_api_key(label=\"a\", rate_limit_per_sec=1, scope=\"admin\")\n242\t    key_b, _ = await make_api_key(label=\"b\", rate_limit_per_sec=100, scope=\"admin\")\n243\t\n244\t    same_ip_transport = ASGITransport(app=app, client=(\"10.0.0.9\", 4000))\n245\t    async with AsyncClient(transport=same_ip_transport, base_url=\"http://test\") as test_client:\n246\t        first = await test_client.get(\"/v1/quotas\", headers={\"Authorization\": f\"Bearer {key_a}\"})\n247\t        second = await test_client.get(\"/v1/quotas\", headers={\"Authorization\": f\"Bearer {key_a}\"})\n248\t        assert first.status_code == 200\n249\t        assert second.status_code == 429\n250\t        assert \"Retry-After\" in second.headers\n251\t\n252\t        b_response = await test_client.get(\"/v1/quotas\", headers={\"Authorization\": f\"Bearer {key_b}\"})\n253\t        assert b_response.status_code == 200, \"principal B, same IP, must have its own untouched bucket\"\n254\t\n255\t        third = await test_client.delete(\n256\t            \"/v1/quotas\",\n257\t            params={\"customer_id\": \"cust_1\", \"metric\": \"api_calls\"},\n258\t            headers={\"Authorization\": f\"Bearer {key_b}\"},\n259\t        )\n260\t        # key_b's bucket has capacity left (100/sec); a 404 (no such quota) is\n261\t        # the expected outcome here, proving the request reached the handler\n262\t        # rather than being throttled.\n263\t        assert third.status_code == 404\n264\t\n265\t\n266\tasync def test_delete_does_not_reset_usage_and_events_uncapped(client, make_api_key, postgres_url):\n267\t    \"\"\"AC13: deleting a quota removes only the cap — `usage_rollup` for that\n268\t    (customer, metric) is unchanged, and a subsequent POST /v1/events for the\n269\t    now-uncapped pair is accepted 201 unlimited (same as never-capped).\"\"\"\n270\t    presented_key, api_key_id = await make_api_key(scope=\"admin\")\n271\t    headers = {\"Authorization\": f\"Bearer {presented_key}\"}\n272\t\n273\t    # Cap it low, then record usage that approaches (but does not exceed) the cap.\n274\t    await _seed_quota(client, headers, customer_id=\"cust_1\", metric=\"api_calls\", limit_per_window=10)\n275\t    event_response = await client.post(\n276\t        \"/v1/events\",\n277\t        json={\n278\t            \"customer_id\": \"cust_1\",\n279\t            \"metric\": \"api_calls\",\n280\t            \"quantity\": \"5\",\n281\t            \"idempotency_key\": \"pre-delete-event\",\n282\t        },\n283\t        headers=headers,\n284\t    )\n285\t    assert event_response.status_code == 201\n286\t\n287\t    from sqlalchemy.ext.asyncio import create_async_engine\n288\t\n289\t    engine = create_async_engine(postgres_url)\n290\t    async with engine.connect() as connection:\n291\t        rollup_before = (\n292\t            await connection.execute(\n293\t                text(\n294\t                    \"SELECT total_quantity FROM usage_rollup WHERE api_key_id = :id \"\n295\t                    \"AND customer_id = 'cust_1' AND metric = 'api_calls'\"\n296\t                ),\n297\t                {\"id\": api_key_id},\n298\t            )\n299\t        ).scalar_one()\n300\t    await engine.dispose()\n301\t    assert rollup_before == 5\n302\t\n303\t    delete_response = await client.delete(\n304\t        \"/v1/quotas\", params={\"customer_id\": \"cust_1\", \"metric\": \"api_calls\"}, headers=headers\n305\t    )\n306\t    assert delete_response.status_code == 204\n307\t\n308\t    engine = create_async_engine(postgres_url)\n309\t    async with engine.connect() as connection:\n310\t        rollup_after = (\n311\t            await connection.execute(\n312\t                text(\n313\t                    \"SELECT total_quantity FROM usage_rollup WHERE api_key_id = :id \"\n314\t                    \"AND customer_id = 'cust_1' AND metric = 'api_calls'\"\n315\t                ),\n316\t                {\"id\": api_key_id},\n317\t            )\n318\t        ).scalar_one()\n319\t    await engine.dispose()\n320\t    assert rollup_after == 5, \"DELETE must never touch usage_rollup\"\n321\t\n322\t    # A large event that would have exceeded the old cap (10) is now accepted\n323\t    # unlimited, since the cap no longer exists.\n324\t    uncapped_response = await client.post(\n325\t        \"/v1/events\",\n326\t        json={\n327\t            \"customer_id\": \"cust_1\",\n328\t            \"metric\": \"api_calls\",\n329\t            \"quantity\": \"9999\",\n330\t            \"idempotency_key\": \"post-delete-event\",\n331\t        },\n332\t        headers=headers,\n333\t    )\n334\t    assert uncapped_response.status_code == 201\n335\t\n336\t\n337\tasync def test_delete_and_forbidden_are_logged(client, make_api_key, capsys):\n338\t    \"\"\"AC16: a successful DELETE logs `quota.delete` INFO (customer_id\n339\t    redacted); a scope-denied GET or DELETE logs the existing `quota.forbidden` WARNING.\"\"\"\n340\t    admin_key, _ = await make_api_key(scope=\"admin\")\n341\t    ingest_key, _ = await make_api_key(label=\"ingest-only\", scope=\"ingest\")\n342\t    headers = {\"Authorization\": f\"Bearer {admin_key}\"}\n343\t    await _seed_quota(client, headers, customer_id=\"cust_1\", metric=\"api_calls\")\n344\t\n345\t    await client.delete(\"/v1/quotas\", params={\"customer_id\": \"cust_1\", \"metric\": \"api_calls\"}, headers=headers)\n346\t    await client.get(\"/v1/quotas\", headers={\"Authorization\": f\"Bearer {ingest_key}\"})\n347\t\n348\t    captured = capsys.readouterr()\n349\t    assert \"quota.delete\" in captured.out\n350\t    assert \"***redacted***\" in captured.out\n351\t    assert \"quota.forbidden\" in captured.out\n352\t\n353\t\n354\tasync def test_openapi_exposes_get_and_delete_quotas(client):\n355\t    \"\"\"AC17 (DAST-readiness): the served /openapi.json includes both GET and\n356\t    DELETE /v1/quotas, matching the implemented routes/schemas.\"\"\"\n357\t    response = await client.get(\"/openapi.json\")\n358\t    assert response.status_code == 200\n359\t    schema = response.json()\n360\t    assert \"/v1/quotas\" in schema[\"paths\"]\n361\t    assert \"get\" in schema[\"paths\"][\"/v1/quotas\"]\n362\t    assert \"delete\" in schema[\"paths\"][\"/v1/quotas\"]\n363\t\n364\t\n365\tasync def test_get_forced_internal_error_returns_safe_envelope(\n366\t    truncate_tables, make_api_key, monkeypatch\n367\t):\n368\t    \"\"\"AC19: a forced internal error during the GET list read returns the\n369\t    generic 500 envelope, with no stack trace / SQL fragment / exception\n370\t    type / internal path leaked.\"\"\"\n371\t    presented_key, _ = await make_api_key(scope=\"admin\")\n372\t\n373\t    from src.services import quota_service\n374\t\n375\t    async def _boom(*args, **kwargs):\n376\t        raise RuntimeError(\"simulated read failure\")\n377\t\n378\t    monkeypatch.setattr(quota_service, \"list_quotas\", _boom)\n379\t\n380\t    from src.main import app\n381\t\n382\t    transport = ASGITransport(app=app, raise_app_exceptions=False)\n383\t    async with AsyncClient(transport=transport, base_url=\"http://test\") as raw_client:\n384\t        response = await raw_client.get(\n385\t            \"/v1/quotas\", headers={\"Authorization\": f\"Bearer {presented_key}\"}\n386\t        )\n387\t\n388\t    assert response.status_code == 500\n389\t    body = response.json()\n390\t    assert body[\"error\"][\"code\"] == \"internal\"\n391\t    assert \"requestId\" in body[\"error\"]\n392\t    message = body[\"error\"][\"message\"].lower()\n393\t    assert \"runtimeerror\" not in message\n394\t    assert \"simulated read failure\" not in message\n395\t    assert \"traceback\" not in message\n396\t\n397\t\n398\tasync def test_delete_forced_internal_error_returns_safe_envelope_and_fails_closed(\n399\t    client, make_api_key, postgres_url, monkeypatch\n400\t):\n401\t    \"\"\"AC19: a forced internal error during DELETE returns the generic 500\n402\t    envelope and fails closed — the transaction rolls back, so the target\n403\t    quota row survives (mirrors test_events_endpoint.py's forced-error test).\"\"\"\n404\t    presented_key, api_key_id = await make_api_key(scope=\"admin\")\n405\t    headers = {\"Authorization\": f\"Bearer {presented_key}\"}\n406\t    await _seed_quota(client, headers, customer_id=\"cust_1\", metric=\"api_calls\", limit_per_window=42)\n407\t\n408\t    from src.services import quota_service\n409\t\n410\t    async def _boom(*args, **kwargs):\n411\t        raise RuntimeError(\"simulated delete failure\")\n412\t\n413\t    monkeypatch.setattr(quota_service, \"delete_quota\", _boom)\n414\t\n415\t    from src.main import app\n416\t\n417\t    transport = ASGITransport(app=app, raise_app_exceptions=False)\n418\t    async with AsyncClient(transport=transport, base_url=\"http://test\") as raw_client:\n419\t        response = await raw_client.delete(\n420\t            \"/v1/quotas\",\n421\t            params={\"customer_id\": \"cust_1\", \"metric\": \"api_calls\"},\n422\t            headers=headers,\n423\t        )\n424\t\n425\t    assert response.status_code == 500\n426\t    body = response.json()\n427\t    assert body[\"error\"][\"code\"] == \"internal\"\n428\t    assert \"requestId\" in body[\"error\"]\n429\t    message = body[\"error\"][\"message\"].lower()\n430\t    assert \"runtimeerror\" not in message\n431\t    assert \"simulated delete failure\" not in message\n432\t    assert \"traceback\" not in message\n433\t\n434\t    from sqlalchemy.ext.asyncio import create_async_engine\n435\t\n436\t    engine = create_async_engine(postgres_url)\n437\t    async with engine.connect() as connection:\n438\t        row = (\n439\t            await connection.execute(\n440\t                text(\n441\t                    \"SELECT limit_per_window FROM quotas WHERE api_key_id = :id \"\n442\t                    \"AND customer_id = 'cust_1' AND metric = 'api_calls'\"\n443\t                ),\n444\t                {\"id\": api_key_id},\n445\t            )\n446\t        ).mappings().one()\n447\t    await engine.dispose()\n448\t    assert row[\"limit_per_window\"] == 42, \"a failed DELETE must leave the target row intact (fail-closed)\"\n449\t\n450\t\n451\tasync def test_concurrent_delete_of_the_same_quota_yields_exactly_one_winner(\n452\t    client, make_api_key, postgres_url\n453\t):\n454\t    \"\"\"AC6/AC7 under contention: N concurrent DELETE requests for the exact\n455\t    same (customer_id, metric) must yield exactly one 204 (the winner) and\n456\t    the rest 404 (the loser's explicit outcome) -- never two 204s (a double\n457\t    side effect) and never a 500/race artifact. Proves the decision point\n458\t    (delete_quota's single parameterized DELETE ... RETURNING) is actually\n459\t    atomic under real concurrent access, not merely correct in the\n460\t    single-caller tests above.\"\"\"\n461\t    presented_key, api_key_id = await make_api_key(scope=\"admin\")\n462\t    headers = {\"Authorization\": f\"Bearer {presented_key}\"}\n463\t    await _seed_quota(client, headers, customer_id=\"cust_race\", metric=\"api_calls\", limit_per_window=100)\n464\t\n465\t    concurrent_requests = 10\n466\t\n467\t    async def _delete():\n468\t        return await client.delete(\n469\t            \"/v1/quotas\", params={\"customer_id\": \"cust_race\", \"metric\": \"api_calls\"}, headers=headers\n470\t        )\n471\t\n472\t    responses = await asyncio.gather(*(_delete() for _ in range(concurrent_requests)))\n473\t    statuses = [response.status_code for response in responses]\n474\t\n475\t    winners = [status for status in statuses if status == 204]\n476\t    losers = [status for status in statuses if status == 404]\n477\t\n478\t    assert len(winners) == 1, f\"expected exactly one 204 winner, got statuses: {statuses}\"\n479\t    assert len(losers) == concurrent_requests - 1, f\"expected the rest to be 404 losers, got statuses: {statuses}\"\n480\t    assert set(statuses) <= {204, 404}, f\"no request should error under contention, got statuses: {statuses}\"\n481\t\n482\t    from sqlalchemy.ext.asyncio import create_async_engine\n483\t\n484\t    engine = create_async_engine(postgres_url)\n485\t    async with engine.connect() as connection:\n486\t        count = (\n487\t            await connection.execute(\n488\t                text(\n489\t                    \"SELECT COUNT(*) FROM quotas WHERE api_key_id = :id \"\n490\t                    \"AND customer_id = 'cust_race' AND metric = 'api_calls'\"\n491\t                ),\n492\t                {\"id\": api_key_id},\n493\t            )\n494\t        ).scalar_one()\n495\t    await engine.dispose()\n496\t    assert count == 0, \"the row must be gone exactly once, not left behind or double-removed\"\n497\t\n498\t\n499\tasync def test_no_new_alembic_migration_added(postgres_url):\n500\t    \"\"\"AC14: this feature operates on the existing `quotas` table — no new\n501\t    file under alembic/versions/ beyond the existing revisions 0001-0003.\"\"\"\n502\t    from pathlib import Path\n503\t\n504\t    versions_dir = Path(__file__).resolve().parents[2] / \"alembic\" / \"versions\"\n505\t    revision_files = sorted(p.name for p in versions_dir.glob(\"*.py\") if not p.name.startswith(\"__\"))\n506\t    assert len(revision_files) == 3, f\"expected exactly 3 migration files, found: {revision_files}\"\n507\t"}]},"uuid":"5b2c9071-141d-4f2e-b15c-026697b145f7","timestamp":"2026-07-10T03:24:49.129Z","sourceToolAssistantUUID":"f1d9050f-2adc-4b3a-9354-11efb92030a8","userType":"external","entrypoint":"claude-vscode","cwd":"c:\\Users\\brett\\OneDrive\\Documents\\GitHub\\meterly-pipeline-test","sessionId":"cb1e5971-0f87-4706-9a1d-09f830df9e6f","version":"2.1.205","gitBranch":"feature/quota-admin"}
