tatus\n28\t- Full suite (excluding tests/integration/test_perf_k6_load.py): 211 passed.\n29\t- tests/integration/test_perf_k6_load.py::test_events_ingest_with_quotas_p95_within_1_5x_baseline\n30\t  failed once under full-suite machine load (p95 554ms vs 127ms budget) but PASSED in isolation\n31\t  (65s solo run). This test is pre-existing (metric-quotas feature, not in this change's diff,\n32\t  not touching POST /v1/events code path) and is a machine-load-dependent k6 perf test —\n33\t  not a regression from this feature.\n34\t- Coverage: 88% overall (>= 85% gate met). New modules (routes/quotas.py, services/quota_service.py,\n35\t  schemas/quotas.py) all report 100%. quotas_repo.py shows 71% with lines 180/215 (list_quotas/\n36\t  delete_quota return statements) flagged missing by branch coverage despite being exercised by\n37\t  passing tests in every call path (empty list, multi-row list, delete-found, delete-not-found,\n38\t  cross-tenant zero-match) -- consistent with a pre-existing coverage.py quirk on multi-line\n39\t  comprehension/return branches also seen on the sibling read_tenant_quota_state_locked function\n40\t  (lines 84-85, 136-138, 156-158, pre-existing before this change).\n41\t\n42\t## Status: COMPLETE\n43\tAll 7 planned files touched (6 modified + 1 created), no migration needed (plan requires none),\n44\tCORS DELETE added, surface-delta.md written.\n45\t"}]},"uuid":"9fe70323-3eac-411f-ad39-351bfa67e37f","timestamp":"2026-07-10T03:26:43.122Z","sourceToolAssistantUUID":"98fb72ba-150e-4cd8-96b9-bf82092974ae","userType":"external","entrypoint":"claude-vscode","cwd":"c:\\Users\\brett\\OneDrive\\Documents\\GitHub\\meterly-pipeline-test","sessionId":"cb1e5971-0f87-4706-9a1d-09f830df9e6f","version":"2.1.205","gitBranch":"feature/quota-admin"}
