{"parentUuid":"04a4dfe3-c6e2-4053-a5b5-a65d302f6049","isSidechain":true,"promptId":"b6d534eb-f80d-405a-a05d-4c7eb6280654","agentId":"a6b206ed2a9ee5b50","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01DmYfoji7pqeAx8wMq2JuN5","type":"tool_result","content":"170\t        text(\n171\t            \"\"\"\n172\t            SELECT customer_id, metric, limit_per_window\n173\t            FROM quotas\n174\t            WHERE api_key_id = :api_key_id\n175\t            ORDER BY customer_id, metric\n176\t            \"\"\"\n177\t        ),\n178\t        {\"api_key_id\": api_key_id},\n179\t    )\n180\t    return [\n181\t        QuotaListItem(\n182\t            customer_id=row[\"customer_id\"],\n183\t            metric=row[\"metric\"],\n184\t            limit_per_window=row[\"limit_per_window\"],\n185\t        )\n186\t        for row in result.mappings().all()\n187\t    ]\n188\t\n189\t\n190\tasync def delete_quota(\n191\t    session: AsyncSession, *, api_key_id: int, customer_id: str, metric: str\n192\t) -> bool:\n193\t    \"\"\"Remove the cap for `(api_key_id, customer_id, metric)`, returning\n194\t    whether a row actually matched and was removed.\n195\t\n196\t    `RETURNING customer_id` on a single-statement, parameterized `DELETE` is\n197\t    what lets the service distinguish \"removed\" from \"nothing there to\n198\t    remove\" without a separate existence check (avoiding a TOCTOU gap\n199\t    between check and delete). The explicit `api_key_id` filter is the\n200\t    primary tenant-confinement control; `quotas_tenant_isolation` FORCE RLS\n201\t    (migration `0003`) is the backstop — a cross-tenant call matches zero\n202\t    rows here, which the service maps to 404 (plan §\"Tenant confinement is\n203\t    structural, not a special case\").\n204\t    \"\"\"\n205\t    result = await session.execute(\n206\t        text(\n207\t            \"\"\"\n208\t            DELETE FROM quotas\n209\t            WHERE api_key_id = :api_key_id AND customer_id = :customer_id AND metric = :metric\n210\t            RETURNING customer_id\n211\t            \"\"\"\n212\t        ),\n213\t        {\"api_key_id\": api_key_id, \"customer_id\": customer_id, \"metric\": metric},\n214\t    )\n215\t    return result.mappings().first() is not None"}]},"uuid":"ed066006-7334-4787-b214-0d69a3da357a","timestamp":"2026-07-10T03:46:18.381Z","sourceToolAssistantUUID":"04a4dfe3-c6e2-4053-a5b5-a65d302f6049","userType":"external","entrypoint":"claude-vscode","cwd":"c:\\Users\\brett\\OneDrive\\Documents\\GitHub\\meterly-pipeline-test","sessionId":"cb1e5971-0f87-4706-9a1d-09f830df9e6f","version":"2.1.205","gitBranch":"feature/quota-admin"}
